did.unittitle: Collection of Bookplates by George W. Eve
did.abstract: This collection contains over two hundred bookplates by British designer and etcher George W. Eve (1855-1914).

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The Yale Bookplate Collection was formerly housed in Sterling Memorial Library. The collection was incorporated into the Arts of the Book Collection in 1984 and then moved to the Seeley G. Mudd Library in 1990. In 2011, it was transferred to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Copyright has not been transferred to Yale University.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Collection of Bookplates by George W. Eve, Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library, Yale University.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The collection was removed from filing cabinets which housed bookplates by individual artists. Some materials included in this collection indicate the provenance of the following bookplate collectors or collections: Irene D. Andrews Pace, George Heath Viner, P. E. Jung, Joseph M. Andreini, Ada Hopson, and the Pearson-Lowenhaupt Collection of English and American Bookplates.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: George William Eve (1855-1914), a British bookplate artist, was an etcher and an expert in the field of heraldry. He was admitted to the Heralds' College as well as to the Royal Society of Painter-Etchers and Engravers. He produced a number of armorial bookplate designs, including a series of three bookplates for the Royal Library at Windsor Castle, which were used by Queen Victoria. Many of his designs were exhibited in Great Britain as well as internationally. He was also the author of Decorative Heraldry; A Practical Handbook of Its Artistic Treatment , published in 1897.
Reference: George H. Viner, A Descriptive Catalogue of the Bookplates Designed and Etched by George W. Eve, R.E. (Kansas City: The American Bookplate Society, 1916), 13-16.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains over 200 bookplates by British designer and etcher George W. Eve (1855-1914). Most of these bookplates are documented in A Descriptive Catalogue of the Bookplates Designed and Etched by George W. Eve, R.E. , authored by George H. Viner and published in 1916. Given his background and expertise in heraldry, most of Eve's bookplates are armorial designs, although several fine pictorial designs, such as library interiors and maritime scenes, are also included.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Organized into four series: I. Bookplates – Numbered. II. Bookplates – Unnumbered. III. Bookplates Attributed to Eve. IV. Correspondence and Ephemera.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Arranged numerically by checklist number – roughly chronological in order. Any correspondence or ephemeral materials relating to a specific bookplate are filed together with the bookplate.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series includes bookplates that are identified and numbered according to the descriptive catalogue published by George Heath Viner in 1916.

scopecontent.p: This series contains several bookplates that were housed together and labeled: "Attributed to Eve." Eve has been identified as the artist for each of these plates by the collector, Irene D. Andrews Pace.
